_data.title: View From Here

children.value: View From Here hired me to work on their 360° Feedback platform. It had previously been built using Perl and benefitted from Perl's superior string parsing and natural language processing capabilities. I suggested migrating to Rails as I'd done a lot of similar work in the more modern framework on my own hobby project, Quotable.

_data.description: Analog and digital clocks, timers and countdowns.
_data.title: Timepiece

children.value: Timepiece is an old project I originally wrote for Ruby on Rails. There, it exposed a Ruby helper that allowed the user to easily drop in a digital or analog clock, a timer, or a countdown into any HTML page with ease. I've been thinking about rewriting the plugin in JavaScript for a long time and have begun the process now as a Nuxt module.

_data.text: Timepiece is an old project I originally wrote for Ruby on Rails. There, it exposed a Ruby helper that allowed the user to easily drop in a digital or analog clock, a timer, or a countdown into any HTML page with ease. I've been thinking about rewriting the plugin in JavaScript for a long time and have begun the process now as a Nuxt module.

_data.title: Playfair

children.value: Playfair is a chart library for Vue.js and Nuxt. Currently it's just a very simple wrapper around vue-chartjs which I would recommend using instead for the time being. Soon, though, I want to remove that dependency and the dependency on Chart.js; I want to reproduce the charts already supported and extend this library even further with D3.js.
